 {"id":"bd-12e.3","title":"Incremental re-render: dirty-region tracking","description":"Track dirty regions across layout changes. Only re-render affected portions of the output. Critical for responsive editing experience.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T17:59:35.101013856Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-07T04:27:14.904852931Z","closed_at":"2026-04-07T04:27:14.904567070Z","close_reason":"Added dirty_regions: Vec<LayoutRect> to DiagramLayout. The incremental layout path (try_incremental_subgraph_relayout) computes dirty region bounds from the changed subgraph regions. Full recompute paths return empty dirty_regions. Renderers can now use dirty_regions to skip re-drawing unchanged portions. 31 construction sites updated across fm-layout, fm-render-svg, fm-render-term, fm-render-canvas.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["frankenmermaid","incremental"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-12e.3","depends_on_id":"bd-12e","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:47Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
